definitions.definition: ( countable ) A small, round, smooth-skinned edible fruit , usually purple, red, or green, that grows in bunches on vines of genus Vitis .
examples: Grapes give us whole-fruit snacks, grape juice, raisins, wine, and more.

definitions.definition: ( countable , uncountable ) A woody vine of genus Vitis that bears clusters of grapes; a grapevine .
examples: wild grape covering the back slope

definitions.definition: ( countable ) Any of various fruits or plants with varying resemblances to those of genus Vitis but belonging to other genera; their edibility varies.
( countable , uncountable ) A dark purplish - red colour , the colour of many grapes.
examples: For those seeking purply tones, the paint colors available include mauve, magenta, and grape .

definitions.definition: ( pathology ) A mangy tumour on a horse 's leg .
( US , naval slang ) A purple-shirted technician responsible for refueling aircraft .
( African-American Vernacular , slang ) A person's head .
